VWith its motto of &#8216;Music to Masses' ( Jan-Jan tak Sangeet), the Sopori Academi of Music, spearheaded by santoor maestro and music composer Pandit Bhajan Sopori, continues tirelessly to organise music-related events. Its annual Sa Ma Pa Sangeet Sammelan, which took place this past weekend, is also an occasion when the organisation and honours senior musicians, musicologists and critics for their service to music. This year the SaMaPa Vitasta Award was presented to maestros Amjad Ali Khan and N. Rajam. The SaMaPa Sher-e-Kashmir Sheikh Mohammad Abdullah Award was presented to Abdul Rashid Qureshi and the SaMaPa Acharya Abhinavgupt Samman was presented to Dr. Mukesh Garg.The award ceremony was followed by Sufi music by vocalist Ragini Rainu, a santoor recital by Abhay Rustam Sopori and a Kuchipudi dance recital by the renowned duo Raja-Radha Reddy. Abhay presented his own creation, raga Nirmal-Kauns, with a detailed alap-jod and a gat in Jai tala of 13 beats.The Bandish &#8220;Jai jai Nirmal Janani&#8221; was written and composed by his guru and father Bhajan Sopori. Tarana in drut Ek tala and a gat in ati drut Teen tala carried the santoor recital to the climax of jhala. Abhay was ably accompanied on the tabla by Abhijit Bannerjee.Among the highlights of the morning session on Sunday was a melodious violin recital by Vidushi N. Rajam who presented raga Devgiri Bilawal with three compositions set to vilambit (slow) Teen tala, madhyalaya (medium tempo) Jhap tala and drut (fast tempo) Teen tala respectively. She concluded her mesmerising recital with the Bhairavi bhajan &#8220;Jogi mat jaa&#8221;, immortalised by her legendary guru, Pandit Omkarnath Thakur.Earlier, a &#8220;Swar-Laya-Samvaad&#8221; conducted by Pandit Vijay Shankar Mishra opened the morning session, in which Zareena Begam, Malini Awasthi and Kimti Lal presented &#8216;&#8220;Thumari Ke Rang&#8221; (colours of the thumri). The concluding session had vocal recitals by Shaunak Abhisheki and Ashwini Bhide and a sitar-flute jugalbandi by Purbayan Chatterjee and Rakesh Chaurasia.
